Posted @withregram • @baeru_environment Our team is so happy and proud to become operators of India’s first rural and coastal waste management facility with a compensation model that will directly benefit the women working in waste. 
As we celebrate our 74th Republic Day, we are honoured to partner with the Udupi Zilla Panchayat and the Government of Karnataka to move the needle for waste workers and coastal communities. 
Waste work can become dignified when the real hands that work are benefitted, not just the aggregators. This is our effort at aligning with equality, which is one of the key founding principles of our democracy.
Please join us in our mission of blue economy for green jobs
Huge thanks to all our mentors and our team most of them who are on the field not even on social media🙏🏽
.

Posted @withrepost • @tip_sessions Beware of Plastic-Asura! 
In 2018, we kicked off our Culture for Climate series with Yakshagana artists to help people of coastal Karnataka understand the value of natural resources around them, and received such a heartfelt response over the last two years! 

We continue to leverage local culture and arts as an important pillar of climate communications at TIP Sessions. Please reach out to us if you’d like to partner with us or volunteer for our climate change work.

latestPosts.caption:
#throwbackmemories: We had the honour of hosting the distinguished Justice Santhosh Hegde at our flagship Yuva Prerana Program. He was very happy to spend the day interacting with 400+ college students from around Udupi District! These students were equally thrilled that they got to spend quality time with him and have all their questions answered! 

He chatted with us about his journey, from his early days as lawyer, to his experience as Supreme Court Judge and Solicitor General of India, and then as Lokayukta. 

What struck me the most was how candid he was with all his responses to each and every question asked by our students. Zero pretense, honest answers (even if you didn’t like what you heard) and full of humility. One of the best sessions we’ve had 🙌🏽

Hoping 2022 will be a better year for interactions such as this one!

#tipsessions #yuvaprerana #lokayukta #youthempowerment
